The paper focuses on enhancing convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image processing tasks, specifically object detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of attention mechanisms in CNNs also involves concepts from neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of feature-based attention, which is a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) technique.
